  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Because that he remembered not to show mercy,.... As Judas did not; neither to the poor, whom he cared not for, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 12:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " nor to Christ, whom he betrayed with a kiss to his enemies: nor had these words of Christ any effect upon him, to move his pity and compassion, \"Friend, wherefore art thou come?\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:49",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " nor did the Jews show mercy to him: they were a merciless and hardhearted people; though mercy was one of the weightier matters of the law, this they omitted, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 23:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", their want of compassion may be observed in the priest and Levite passing by the man wounded by thieves, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 10:30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Nor did they show any mercy to Christ, when they smote and buffeted him; nor did it move their pity when Pilate brought him forth with a crown of thorns on his head, and in a miserable condition, saying, \"Behold the man\"; but they cried out, \"Crucify him, crucify him\"; and gave him gall for his meat, and vinegar to drink; and mocked him when in all his miseries and agonies. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But persecuted the poor and needy man; Christ, who became poor for our sakes, and stood in need of the ministration of others to him, 2 Corinthians 8:9 and was poor in spirit, a man of sorrows, and acquainted with griefs; him Judas and the Jews persecuted to death, as follows: ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "But persecuted the poor and needy man; Christ, who became poor for our sakes, and stood in need of the ministration of others to him, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Corinthians 8:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " and was poor in spirit, a man of sorrows, and acquainted with griefs; him Judas and the Jews persecuted to death, as follows: ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that he might even slay the broken in heart; Christ, whose heart was broken with the reproach and cruel usage of men, Psalm 69:20, whose life the Jews sought to take away, and by means of Judas did. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "that he might even slay the broken in heart; Christ, whose heart was broken with the reproach and cruel usage of men, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
